{"key":"processedPost-12064154","value":{"id":12064154,"first":12063572,"last":12071323,"when":1266677170,"utime":"02/20/10 04:46 PM","content":"First of all, casing is of dubious benefit to cubensis anyway.&nbsp; Species which don't require a casing layer benefit little from applying one.&nbsp; Stick to 12/12 for light.&nbsp; Don't use 24 or especially 48.&nbsp; If you fruit uncased, the entire top of the substrate is exposed to fresh air and light.&nbsp; Mist to make up for the lost moisture.&nbsp; Casing can help supply moisture to support a flush, but so can soaking and/or misting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pinning trigger time"}}